---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy | The Princeton Journal">
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-10">
    <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-500">
      Privacy Policy
    </p>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>

    <div class="article-content mt-8 text-lg leading-8 text-gray-800">
      <p>
        The Princeton Journal respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains, in general terms, how information may be collected, used, and handled when you visit this website or contact us.
      </p>

      <p>
        By using this website, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Information You Provide Voluntarily</h2>

      <p>
        If you contact The Princeton Journal by email or through a contact form, you may choose to provide information such as your name, email address, subject line, message content, and any documents or materials you submit.
      </p>

      <p>
        This information may be used to:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>respond to your message or inquiry</li>
        <li>review tips, documents, or corrections</li>
        <li>communicate with you about your submission</li>
        <li>maintain records related to correspondence</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Information Collected Automatically</h2>

      <p>
        Like most websites, this site may automatically receive limited technical information from your browser or device, such as your IP address, browser type, operating system, referring pages, and general usage information.
      </p>

      <p>
        This type of information may be used for basic site administration, security, troubleshooting, analytics, and improvement of the website.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>

      <p>
        This website may use basic cookies or similar technologies that are necessary for site functionality, performance, analytics, or security.
      </p>

      <p>
        Your browser settings may allow you to limit, disable, or delete cookies. Disabling cookies may affect how certain parts of the site function.
      </p>

      <h2>Email Communications</h2>

      <p>
        If you email The Princeton Journal or submit a message through the site, your communication may be retained for editorial, administrative, legal, or recordkeeping purposes.
      </p>

      <p>
        Sending information to The Princeton Journal does not create a confidential, fiduciary, or privileged relationship.
      </p>

      <h2>Tips, Documents, and Submitted Materials</h2>

      <p>
        Materials submitted to The Princeton Journal may be reviewed, verified, and retained. Submission of information does not guarantee publication, response, or ongoing communication.
      </p>

      <p>
        The Princeton Journal may use submitted materials for reporting, verification, research, or editorial review, subject to applicable law and editorial judgment.
      </p>

      <h2>How Information May Be Shared</h2>

      <p>
        The Princeton Journal does not sell personal information to third parties.
      </p>

      <p>
        Information may be disclosed when reasonably necessary to:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>operate, maintain, or secure the website</li>
        <li>respond to legal obligations, lawful requests, or court orders</li>
        <li>protect the rights, safety, property, or integrity of The Princeton Journal, its readers, or others</li>
        <li>investigate abuse, fraud, or misuse of the website</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Third Party Services</h2>

      <p>
        This website may rely on third party services or platforms for hosting, email, analytics, or other technical functions. Those services may have their own privacy practices and policies.
      </p>

      <p>
        The Princeton Journal is not responsible for the privacy practices of third party websites, services, or platforms not directly controlled by this site.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Security</h2>

      <p>
        Reasonable efforts may be taken to protect information submitted through the website, but no method of internet transmission or electronic storage can be guaranteed as completely secure.
      </p>

      <p>
        Users should avoid sending sensitive personal, financial, medical, or legally privileged information unless they understand and accept the risks of electronic communication.
      </p>

      <h2>Children’s Privacy</h2>

      <p>
        This website is not directed to children under the age of 13, and The Princeton Journal does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 through the site.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Choices</h2>

      <p>
        You may choose not to submit personal information through the website. You may also contact The Princeton Journal if you have questions about communications you have sent through the site.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any updated version will be posted on this page with the revised effective date.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>

      <p>
        For privacy-related questions or general inquiries, contact:
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>theprincetonjournal@gmail.com</strong>
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p>
        Effective date: March 10, 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
